INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('6617916','2018-01-03','On a windy, rainswept night this was a warm and inviting retreat. Schnitzel is the speciality of the house and they have many variations. I had the Munich variation and it was exactly what I was looking for. Tasty, hearty German food. One of the most satisfying meals I’ve had out in a very long time   Friendly, attentive staff and was pleasantly busy on a miserable, midweek evening. Highly recommended.','5');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('6617916','2017-09-23','Allegedly the place is owned by a gay couple, and seems to be situated in a gay area of Berlin (supported by the colourful businesses that surround it), but that should have no bearing on your choice to eat at this fine restaurant. The food is well-prepared and the portions are fit for a truly satisfying meal. Along with that, the staff are quite friendly and service is fairly fast. There''s a reason Elefant is rated highly overall; I''d have given 5 stars if only they hadn''t first sent me the wrong plate.','4');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('6617916','2017-10-28','I had the Pork Paris Style. The meat was too well done and kind of dry. But sides and croquettes were fine. The place was crowded with homosexuals, some of which had physical interactions with the waitors. I prefer the service to bee much more professional. Main course around 14 EUR.','2');
