INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('49303307','2017-08-30','Good service, great atmosphere, but average and expensive food. My impression it''s a trendy hipsters place, my partner said it''s a tourist trap. We took a menu with soup, schnitzel and strudel, only schnitzel was good, fresh and soft. Pumpkin soup was tasteless, my grandma would definitely cook better. Strudel also had absolutely plane sugar-free taste, but it came with cream, so I could finish it. On top of all they serve vegan gluten-free beer (never tried this before). It has nice yeast flavor and 5.3% of alcohol, however it felt like 0% without any bitterness, so I''d prefer something more common (hey, we''re in Germany!). So unlike many other reviews we wouldn''t recommend this place if you''re visiting Berlin and looking for some local food.','2');
