INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('27928308','2017-10-12','Had just an exceptional meal at Lokal.  You walk into this cool little bistro and you could be in the W Village of NY or the W Bank of Paris.  Great atmosphere and the name belays the overall feel.  Definitely feels like a local spot.  I have been to Germany a number of times and always seemed to get roped into a "traditional German" meal, so sausages, potatoes etc.  Lokal finally gave me a taste of "modern German."  I had a roast bore dish that mixed flavors from E Europe and Germany, complete with sauerkraut and borsch sauce.  It was excellent.  Not heavy but filling with some fun peppers to round out the dish.  My dinner mate had the Hake dish which he devoured.  We only had mains but saw some other awesome dishes getting served around us.  Highly recommend this place!  And prices are super reasonable.','5');
