INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('76008626','2017-08-31','We absolutely loved the look of this restaurant, the ambience and service was lovely, our waitress was enchanting. However we chose the wrong dishes, both fish. Bland and tasteless, sadly.  However wine and coffee superb.  The reviews were we read related to pizza or pasta. Please don''t be put off by our review - choose wisely.','2');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('76008626','2017-08-04','The food here is nice and the service was very friendly. I had the amatriciana which was a bit spicy but lovely. I would skip the garlic bread if I went again however. The tiramisu was great. The waitress was very nice. The patio is lovely in good weather. ','4');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('76008626','2016-11-18','Our experience was unbelievable!  We had 21 people in our group and 18 were hungry high school students. Our server, Susann Sievert, was so friendly, outgoing and helpful. She got our group right in and gave great suggestions of what to order. The food was delicious and the dessert was wonderful. I only wish I could give more than 5 stars! I highly recommend eating at Marcellino!','5');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('76008626','2017-02-15','Very friendly service. The food is well made and affordable. Great pizza. Good appetizers. Delicious desserts.','5');
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('76008626','2016-10-01','Cheerful yellow-checked tablecloths reflect the warmth and friendliness of the staff at this cosy, informal and warm Italian cafe. It''s tucked away in a quiet leafy courtyard which gives it a secluded feel. I ate here on a dark wet September evening but I can imagine that on a warm summers evening a seat outside would be a treat. I started with the chefs salad which was very fresh and well dressed. The steak was ordered and cooked medium, a rarity in Germany where medium usually means well-done. The vegetables were crisp and again obviously fresh that day. The Tiramisu lacks a little of the alcohol kick one might expect but is by no means poor. I''ve spent a pleasant two and a half hours here, and never felt rushed. Marcellino is bookmarked for my next trip to Berlin. ','5');
