INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('56608699','2017-10-17','Attention Google diners.  Please do not rate if you a) order fries and beer, b) do not know how to cook for yourself or eat purely for sustenance rather than enjoyment.  I was tricked into coming to this restaurant due to it''s 4.6 / 5 rating, a rating that some 1-star Michelen restaurants don''t get.  Arrived at 17:50 for a 18:00 reservation, was told to wait outside until the restaurant officially opened (opening time 18:00).  I could understand this if they were still setting up, but they were just chilling.  Ordered a Maultaschen Suppe... did not come with a spoon... couldn''t find our waiter until the soup was cold.  Ordered the roast pork and duck.  1/2 Duck was ok, but a bit dried out which is amazing since duck is such a fatty meat and is hard to overcook.  Pork roast was dried out and only edible with their excessively salted gravy.  This is not a case of "this person doesn''t like German food".  I love German food, especially Maultaschen, Duck and Roasts.  I''m just never going to eat it at this restaurant and neither should you.  The only plus was that all the food seemed to be "homemade".','2');
