INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('93575769','2017-09-30','Like so many others, we wanted to see the remarkable Reichstag building but had not requested tickets the many weeks earlier it would have taken.  Our concierge (the fabulous Tim at the Berlin Hilton) did manage to get us Saturday Night reservations at the restaurant which allows a tour of the building.  Our experience was nothing short of excellent. In fairness, our reservation were early (7:00) and the place was still empty so the service was luxurious with great attention being paid to us in the selection of dishes and wines.  
INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('93575769','2017-11-24','We visited the restaurant on 20 Nov 2017 for my wife''s birthday but only had a main course each due to the outrageous prices. From a limited choice, my wife had venison and I had duck. We also had a 0.75L bottle of water to share (which cost 9.50euros). Our bill came to over 74euros!! I must say the meat was delicious and melted in the mouth but the dinner portions were small and I could easily have eaten the same again. At first I though the high prices must include entry fee to the dome, however this was not the case, as entry is free.','2');
