INSERT INTO "USER_REVIEW" ("RESTAURANT_ID","REVIEW_DATE","COMMENT","REVIEW_RATING")VALUES('53484463','2017-08-11','Best Vietnamese restaurant hands-down. Family- run, delicious and fresh food.  I highly recommend the pancakes with tofu (wrapped in lettuce leaves), Banh uot (ricepaper wraps with pork and mushroom), glass noodle dish with prawns,  and the duck noodles.  Value for money is super high- especially considering the quality of the ingredients. I go here at least once a week and it''s been my staple here in Berlin. Outdoor seating when the weather is nice, and the interior has these beautiful historical tiles. The two sons who run the restaurant are the nicest guys - and the mom in the kitchen is just amazing. It''s a rare find to see a restaurant operated with so much love and each family member contributing such a large part of the success of this place.  Wish I could rate this place higher than 5 stars because it deserves every accolade it gets.','5');
